<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-06-30T12:22:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-06-30T12:22:00-05:00" n="179" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d179">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/6–3050: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Joint Chiefs of Staff</gloss> to
                            the Commander in Chief, Far East</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacArthur</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">emergency</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-06-30T13:22:00-04:00">30 June
                                1950—1:22 p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>JCS 84718. Restrictions on use of Army Forces imposed by JCS 84681<note n="1" xml:id="d179fn1">Transmitted on June 29 at 6:59 p. m., <ref target="#pg_240">p. 240</ref>.</note> are hereby removed and
                        authority granted to utilize Army Forces available to you as proposed your C
                            56942<note n="2" xml:id="d179fn2">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_248">p. 248</ref>.</note>
                        subject only to requirements for safety of Japan in the present situation
                        which is a matter for your judgment.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>